name: Random.String

values.name: anyCapitalizedEnglishWord
values.comment:
Generate a random capitalized word with english characters of random length
between 1 34.
Aside: 34 was picked as a maximum as "supercalifragilisticexpialidocious"
is considered the longest commonly used word and is 34 character long.
Longer words do occur, especially in scientific contexts. In which case, consider
using `rangeLengthEnglishWord` for more granular control.

values.name: anyEnglishWord
values.comment:
Generate a random lowercase word with english characters of random length
between 1 34.
Aside: 34 was picked as a maximum as "supercalifragilisticexpialidocious"
is considered the longest commonly used word and is 34 character long.
Longer words do occur, especially in scientific contexts. In which case, consider
using `rangeLengthEnglishWord` for more granular control.

values.name: capitalizedEnglishWord
values.comment:
Generate a random capitalized word with english characters of a given length.
Note: This just generates a random string using the letters in english, so there
are no guarantees that the result be an actual english word.

values.name: englishWord
values.comment:
Generate a random lowercase word with english characters of a given length.
Note: This just generates a random string using the letters in english, so there
are no guarantees that the result be an actual english word.

values.name: rangeLengthCapitalizedEnglishWord
values.comment:
Generate a random capitalized word with english characters of random length
given a minimum length and a maximum length.

values.name: rangeLengthEnglishWord
values.comment:
Generate a random lowercase word with english characters of random length
given a minimum length and maximum length.

values.name: rangeLengthString
values.comment:
Generates a random string of random length given the minimum length
and maximum length and a given character generator.
values.type: Int -> Int -> Random.Generator Char -> Random.Generator String

values.name: string
values.comment:
Generate a random string of a given length with a given character generator

    fiveLetterEnglishWord = string 5 english

name: Random.Set

values.name: empty
values.comment: Generator that always returns the empty set

values.name: notInSet
values.comment: Filter a generator of all values not in a given set.
values.type: Set.Set comparable -> Random.Generator comparable -> Random.Generator comparable

values.name: select
values.comment:
Select a value from a set uniformly at random, or `Nothing` for an empty set.
Analogous to `Random.Extra.select` but with sets.

values.name: selectWithDefault
values.comment:
Select a value from a set uniformly at random, with a default.
Analogous to `Random.Extra.selectWithDefault` but with sets.

values.name: set
values.comment:
Generate a set of at most the given size from a generator.

The size of a generated set is limited both by the integer provided and the
number of unique values the generator can produce. It is very likely, but not
guaranteed, that generated sets will be as big as the smaller of these two limits.

values.name: singleton
values.comment: Generator that creates a singleton set from a generator

name: Random.Maybe

values.name: maybe
values.comment: Generate a Maybe from a generator. Will generate Nothings 50% of the time.

values.name: withDefault
values.comment: Generate values from a maybe generator or a default value.

values.name: withDefaultGenerator
values.comment: Generate values from a maybe generator or a default generator.
values.type: Random.Generator a -> Random.Generator (Maybe.Maybe a) -> Random.Generator a

values.type: Int -> Int -> Random.Generator a -> Random.Generator (List a)

name: Random.Order

values.name: order
values.comment: Generate a random order with equal probability.

name: Random.Result

values.name: error
values.comment: Generate an error result from a random generator of errors

values.name: ok
values.comment: Generate an ok result from a random generator of values

values.name: result
values.comment:
Generate an ok result or an error result with 50-50 chance

This is simply implemented as follows:

    result errorGenerator okGenerator =
      frequency
        [ (1, error errorGenerator)
        , (1, ok okGenerator)
        ] (ok okGenerator)

If you want to generate results with a different frequency, tweak those
numbers to your bidding in your own custom generators.
values.type: Random.Generator error -> Random.Generator value -> Random.Generator (Result.Result error value)

Generate a random Character in the valid unicode range.

Sample without replacement: produce a randomly selected element of the
array, and the array with that element omitted (shifting all later elements

values.name: sample
values.comment:
Sample with replacement: produce a randomly selected element of the
array, or `Nothing` for an empty array. Takes O(1) time.

values.name: shuffle
values.comment:
Shuffle the array using the Fisher-Yates algorithm. Takes O(_n_ log _n_)
time and O(_n_) additional space.

values.name: frequency
values.comment:
Create a generator that chooses a generator from a tuple of generators
based on the provided likelihood. The likelihood of a given generator being
chosen is its likelihood divided by the sum of all likelihood. A default
generator must be provided in the case that the list is empty or that the
sum of the likelihoods is 0. Note that the absolute values of the likelihoods
is always taken.
values.type: List ( Float, Random.Generator a ) -> Random.Generator a -> Random.Generator a

values.name: generateIterativelyUntil
